subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
A medium-sized species of 

Rhinella

(

Figs. 
1

A–B, 
2
A–G) distinguished by the following unique combination of characteristics: (
1
) canthus rostralis concave in dorsal view, sharp in profile, orbitotympanic and postorbital crests prominent, not protruding; (
2
) tympanum distinct, oval; (
3
) parotoid glands large, oblong to subtriangular, protuberant, separated from eyelid and tympanum by the supratympanic crest; (
4
) body surfaces covered by spiny tubercles with keratinized tips; (
5
) extremities long and slender; (
6
) a dorsolateral row of conical, enlarged, and elevated tubercles; (
7
) tarsal fold absent; (
8
) webbing absent on fingers, basal and serrated between toes; (
9
) first finger longer than second; (
10
) iris green in life.
